703683f-a.text:
Clinton Street, st the S.W. corner of Kane Street, showing the Christ Protestant Episcopal Church. The cornerstone was laid in 1842. Richard Upjohn is the architect. For additional data see 'The New York Times,"February 26, 1939.

On the right is Kane Street, viewing westward.

View 3 is east on Kane Street from Strong Place.

View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection October, 1928

Views 2,3: P. L. Sperr
View 2: August 5, 1934
View 3: October 15, 1940
